metadata.name: Ghocities
metadata.description:
Second generative art collection by Ttozatto. It was made only with p5.js, all in 2D.

This collection is mainly a study of isometric projections.

There are 8 fixed color palletes and 3 light filters.
Light intensity in each face of the buildings vary.
The buildings are generated in a fixed grid.
Highs and lows are rare.
Collisions are welcome here!

metadata.name: KhromArt
metadata.description:
This project is based on abstract art and color studies. One of the palette is inspired by a Paul Klee painting, "Castle and Sun". 


Main features include:
- Grid division: 3 x 3, 4 x 4 or 5 x 5
- Texture : True or False
- Color Palettes : 8 


The 8 possible color palettes, including the Paul Klee palette, are the following:
- Klee
- Landscape
- Ocean
- Earth & Water
- Sunset
- Nature
- Grayscale
- Summer

In live mode, press [s] to save a 1024 x 1024 version of the mint.

a composition made in MS Paint with primitive rectangles and just one variation for each one: on or off.

metadata.name: Coryphaeus
metadata.description:
We have a population of agents programmed to keep their direction and speed of movement as long as they are not colliding with others. When an agent gets too close to other agent, tries to avoid it. When they get to the margin of the canvas they bounce. There are times when, pushed by crowds, an agent leaves the canvas. Then, it dies.

Some agents follow a leader. When their speed is bigger than the leader's the spiraling patterns emerge. When a leader dies all its followers are captured by another one. A migration can be observed then.

Algorithm only shows the leaders and followers. The rest of the crowd is vastly dimmed.


Features:
Agents: the total number of agents.
Followers: the percent of population that are followers
Leadership: percent of population that are leaders
Society Model: Equality & Diversity. In "Equality" model, all agents have the same speed. Diversity: random speeds.
Palette: the colors or the lack of.

Vanilla javascript. The only package used is @liamegan1/fxhash-helpers licensed under MIT

metadata.name: Beachscape
metadata.description:
A generative beach with palms, mountains, cities, a dynamic nightsky and an animated shore.

Position of sun and moon are based on your local system time, so the artworks looks different depending on which time of the day it is loaded.

Artwork varies in palm-count,cloud constellation, mountain-silhouette, city-size, and overall color-scheme and nightsky density.

Press 'space' or click/tap to shift time by 6h.

In Live-View...

...press 's' to save a high-res version of the current rendering
...press 'n' to let the stars draw their paths.
...press 'p' for a color-sliced background
...press 'f' to switch between fixed and responsive ratio of the rendering.
...press 'r' and allow location-access to get an approximation for your local sunset/sunrise time.

- @TeNinEightNFTs


Created with p5.js using p5.createloop, p5.collide2d and map2.

metadata.name: illusions
metadata.description:
"illusions" is an experiment with textures made from grains, flows and noise, which slowly forms into an abstract figure. 
It can resemble clouds, nebulae, waterfalls, neon bars and anything else your brain can imagine while looking at it.

The growth and formation patterns of "illusions" are 3:
They can grow in the form of a cloud, in the form of lines/squares or just a noise, and also in a glitch effect.

There are 11 color palettes and one of them is monochromatic in black/white, it is the rarest as there is only 4% chance of happening.

You can open the live view to have a better experience.
-Also in live view you can press the "s" key to save a .png file of the artwork.

Works properly on Chrome.

This is an artwork in p5.js.



Omar Lobato Neto, 10/03/2022

metadata.name: Sketchbook Splash
metadata.description:
A splash of color on some scribbled shapes.

There are several keybindings to modify the image:
'1' - Toggles watercolors
'2' - Toggles overlaying constrast shapes 
'3' - Toggles sketch outlines
'4' - Toggles shape/splatter clipping (will fill the entire canvas with watercolor!)
'B' - Cycles borders; black, white, all colors in the palette being used, and no border

Play around to find something you like, and then press 'S' to download a copy of your image. 
You can also modify the URL parameters at the end of the URL to change the size of the image, such as &x=2560&y=1440. Keep in mind that this will result in a slightly different image, but colors/shapes/general layout will remain the same. The default size is 2048x2048.

@teaboswell, 2022

For third party license information, please see bundle.js.LICENSE.txt

metadata.name: Through a Pixel, Darkly
metadata.description:
"Through a Pixel, Darkly" is a small experimental generative art piece that attempts to highlight some of the inherent contradictions surrounding the discussion of non-fungible tokens (NFTs) and its place as a vehicle for artistic creation, artistic expression and the potential of remuneration for artists.

Controls:

r - reset animation

s - take screenshot

a - save animation (advanced users)


To the extent possible, the source code is dedicated to the public domain (CC0) and can be used for any purpose, even commercial, by anyone. Third party libraries are used that are not under a CC0 license but instead are libre/free licensed, allowing for commercial reuse (please see the LICENSE section for more details).

Arguments against NFTs and cryptocurrencies are often against aspects of the financial system but, instead, focus on NFTs and cryptocurrencies that are replicating or complementing those services. Criticisms against NFTs and cryptocurrencies that can be easily supplanted with central banks, cash, credit card companies, online market places, online payment processors or money transfer services are not arguments against NFTs or cryptocurrencies, specifically, but against a general financial system.

Many aspects of NFTs and cryptocurrencies deserve scrutiny, criticism, oversight and critical assessment. When arguments against NFTs and cryptocurrencies use the same tactics of psychological manipulation, emotional pleas and coercion, it does a disservice to anyone pursing truth.

This work hopes to add to the conversation about examining the reality of the ecosystem that we've developed around digital goods and intellectual property.

metadata.name: Boundary Swirl
metadata.description:
Inspired by the swirling eelgrass beds of Boundary Bay with a splash of color stolen from a spring sunset mixed in. 

Boundary Swirl is carefully designed so it can transform into an In-Real-Life 12 layer woodcut that you can hold, touch, and smell.
 
üëâ The 10 rarest mints will receive a free woodcut signed by the artist.
 
Woodcuts for all mints can be requested by owners at: https://alleditions.art/fxhash/u18ipyeo

The potential palette for the IRL woodcut includes the World's Blackest Black (Black 3.0) by Stuart Semple. 

Keyboard shortcuts:
shift S - save SVG for plotting or laser cutting
shift P - save PNG for sharing 
shift E - explode the layers

metadata.name: Psy Sym Blotter
metadata.description:
Psychedelic Symmetrical Blotter art generator with interactive drawing functions. The 1:1 output is saved at 4500 x 4500 pixels which prints 7.5 x 7.5 inch blotter sheets @ 600 dpi. Perforation marks (which can be turned off) divide the sheet into 900 quarter inch hits/tabs. When the display is put in fullscreen, the default 1:1 aspect ratio is stretched to fill the screen, but perforations are not shown. Even though the default canvas is drawn with quad symmetry, a secondary quad symmetry display can be enabled to take the blotter art to the next level. Interactive drawing functions are shown once the token is minted.

March 2022
coded by StreamDreamz (a.k.a. Freakiebeat)
coded with - html, css, javascript, p5.js

License: NFT License 2.0
metadata.childrenDescription:
Psychedelic Symmetrical Blotter art generator with interactive drawing functions. The 1:1 output is saved at 4500 x 4500 pixels which prints 7.5 x 7.5 inch blotter sheets @ 600 dpi. Perforation marks (which can be turned off) divide the sheet into 900 quarter inch hits/tabs. When the display is put in fullscreen, the default 1:1 aspect ratio is stretched to fill the screen, but perforations are not shown. Even though the default canvas is drawn with quad symmetry, a secondary quad symmetry display can be enabled to take the blotter art to the next level. Interactive drawing functions are shown once the token is minted.

All features can be manipulated interactively using the keyboard.
- Space key or mouse click starts/stops puck drawing
- 'q' or 'Q' - secondary quad symmetry (on/off)
- 'r' or 'R' - rotate quad symmetry by 90 degrees
- 'p' or 'P' - auto pausing function (on/off)
- 'x' or 'X' - show perforations (on/off)
- 'c' or 'C' - select random puck color
- 'a' or 'A' - random color on all puck draws (on/off)
- 'b' or 'B' - color banding (on/off)
- 'm' or 'M' - puck modulation (on/off)
- 't' or 'T' - cycles transparency (none/light/medium)
- '1' - slowest (1 fps) puck drawing
- '2' - slower (10 fps) puck drawing
- '3' - faster (30 fps) puck drawing
(fps rate may not be accurate if quad symmetry enabled)
- 's' or 'S' - save 4500 x 4500 pixel png image
(print size = 7.5 x 7.5 inches @ 600 dpi)
(fullscreen saved images are screen dimensions X 2)
- 'n' or 'N' - re-initializes the gentk

Rarity features are written to the console at loading and whenever changed interactively.

March 2022
coded by StreamDreamz (a.k.a. Freakiebeat)
coded with - html, css, javascript, p5.js

License: NFT License 2.0

metadata.name: Textile Bacteria
metadata.description:
Telar's code became self-aware and tried to escape. I built a containment unit. "Textile Bacteria" is the result.

--

The piece is based on the 1970's work of the British mathematician John Conway's "Conway's Game of Life" cellular automaton. To avoid bacteria from dying when one of the threads ends up entirely on top of the other the algorithm adds one pseudorandom artificial cross in the weaving feeding the creatures keeping at the same time the weave consistent.

- Left-click to feed dead bacteria.
- Use the arrow keys to flip between the face and the back of the fabric.
- Press 'SPACE' on your keyboard to pause/play. 
- Press 'ENTER' on your keyboard to rewind. 
- Press 'F' on your keyboard to toggle between full-screen and regular view. 
- Press 'S' on your keyboard to save it as a 36 megapixels print.

metadata.name: YouAreAMazing1.0
metadata.description:
YouAreAMazing1.0 

 Playable, colorful, and often *very challenging* generative-art mazes.
   
 Each maze begins with an "intro" animation of its genesis when opened.
   
 Mazes range in size from from "normal" to "MASSIVE".
   They're made of colorful interconnected rooms.
   Some mazes are spacious, others are downright claustrophobic.
   Floors are colored using 1 of 16 palettes of varying rarities.
   
   Some mazes feature a cat.
   

   Each twist and turn of every maze is randomly chosen,
     so there are BILLIONS of possible mazes.
      
   
   
   ... oh yeah, they're also playable ...
   
   keyboard:
   wasd keys navigate
   'h' peeks (cheats)
   
   touchscreen:
   touch edges to navigate
   top-right corner to peek (cheat)
   
   
   To PRINT your maze, press 'p'
   This will temporarily display the maze & its features in monochrome
     and open the 'print' dialog.
   
   When you complete your maze, you may save a file
     to remind people that "amazing you are"!
   
   
   ** Thanks to Jamis Buck, whose blog posts and interactive demos
       are informative, entertaining and inspiring! 
       I highly recommend checking out his blog: weblog.jamisbuck.org

  ** This is my genesis on FxHash, and I hope you love it! Please let me know if you have any issues interacting with your maze and I'll be happy to help!

metadata.name: The Good Half
metadata.description:
This is a generative art conceptualised by https://twitter.com/probfactory and coded by https://twitter.com/dgenartist.

Prob is a User Experience designer by day and a Graphic artist and a Typographer at night.

DG loves art and loves generative art even more as it involves code, Math and never fails to surprise the eyes on each run.

This art is a representation of our love for typography and letters.
